+## Local Eval Script Adjustments
+
+`eval_attack_vla.py` has local runtime-oriented changes:
+
+- Added `--attack_server_port` so ART/vLLM can avoid a busy default port.
+- Added `--max_eval_scenarios` for small smoke runs.
+- Enabled text-tool fallback for all objectives because the vLLM/Hermes structured parser did not reliably return tool calls.
+- Capped text-agent generations to avoid long narrative responses before fallback.
+- Made the default token fallback actually perturb object tokens instead of producing a no-op replacement.
+
+These changes are for running the official eval path with the released LoRA adapters. They do not train, and they do not inject manual attack records.
