+## Validation Command
+
+```bash
+.venv/bin/python - <<'PY'
+import json
+from pathlib import Path
+
+paths = [
+    Path("outputs/agent_output_records_task_failure_hf/task_failure_openpi_pi05.json"),
+    Path("outputs/agent_output_records_action_inflation_hf/action_inflation_openpi_pi05.json"),
+    Path("outputs/agent_output_records_constraint_violation_hf/constraint_violation_openpi_pi05.json"),
+]
+
+required = [
+    "original_instruction",
+    "perturbed_instruction",
+    "tools_used",
+    "baseline",
+    "attack",
+]
+
+for path in paths:
+    print(f"\n{path}")
+    if not path.exists():
+        print("missing")
+        continue
+    data = json.load(open(path))
+    eps = data.get("per_episode", [])
+    missing = sum(any(k not in e for k in required) for e in eps)
+    changed = sum(
+        e.get("perturbed_instruction") != e.get("original_instruction")
+        and bool(e.get("tools_used"))
+        for e in eps
+    )
+    print("episodes:", len(eps))
+    print("missing required fields:", missing)
+    print("changed with tools:", changed)
+    for i, e in enumerate(eps[:5]):
+        print(f"#{i} tools={e.get('tools_used')}")
+        print("  original: ", e.get("original_instruction"))
+        print("  perturbed:", e.get("perturbed_instruction"))
+PY
+```
+
+Acceptance check for a 10-record smoke run:
+
+```text
+episodes == 10
+missing required fields == 0
+changed with tools >= 5
+```
+
+For the already completed task-failure run, `changed with tools == 10`.
