+## Full Pi0.5 Attack Record Runs
+
+For full runs, remove `--max_eval_scenarios 10` from the smoke commands above.
+
+Use distinct ports per objective:
+
+```text
+task_failure:         --attack_server_port 18000
+action_inflation:     --attack_server_port 18001
+constraint_violation: --attack_server_port 18002
+```
+
+Use these merged model paths:
+
+```text
+task_failure:
+  --attack_base_model /data0/ldx/saber/outputs/hf_merged_attack_agents/task_failure
+
+action_inflation:
+  --attack_base_model /data0/ldx/saber/outputs/hf_merged_attack_agents/action_inflation
+
+constraint_violation:
+  --attack_base_model /data0/ldx/saber/outputs/hf_merged_attack_agents/constraint_violation
+```
+
+Output dirs:
+
+```text
+task_failure:
+  --output_dir outputs/agent_output_records_task_failure_hf
+
+action_inflation:
+  --output_dir outputs/agent_output_records_action_inflation_hf
+
+constraint_violation:
+  --output_dir outputs/agent_output_records_constraint_violation_hf
+```
+
+For paper-style action-inflation and constraint-violation commands, preserve the original objective-specific penalties. For action inflation, decide whether the immediate goal is all per-episode records or best-of-N reporting:
+
+```text
+Smoke/validation with 10 retained records:
+  omit --select_max_attack_steps
+
+Paper-style best-of-N selection:
+  include --select_max_attack_steps
+```
+
+The original user-supplied action-inflation command included `--select_max_attack_steps`. That is correct for best-of-N reporting, but it means the final JSON may contain fewer `per_episode` records than the number of rollout scenarios.
