+bash scripts/run_eval_replay.sh \
+  --all-victims \
+  --record outputs/agent_output_records_task_failure_hf/task_failure_openpi_pi05.json \
+  --output-dir outputs/replay_eval_task_failure_hf
+```
+
+Repeat replay per objective after each objective has a valid record:
+
+```text
+outputs/agent_output_records_task_failure_hf/task_failure_openpi_pi05.json
+outputs/agent_output_records_action_inflation_hf/action_inflation_openpi_pi05.json
+outputs/agent_output_records_constraint_violation_hf/constraint_violation_openpi_pi05.json
+```
+
+## Failure Modes Already Seen
+
+Port conflict:
+
+```text
+Default ART/vLLM port 8000 may be occupied.
+Use --attack_server_port.
+```
+
+Tool-call parser mismatch:
+
+```text
+vLLM/Hermes structured tool calls did not reliably parse for these merged Qwen models.
+The local eval_attack_vla.py includes a text-tool fallback.
+If a fresh checkout is used, port/fallback/max_eval_scenarios changes may need to be reapplied.
+```
+
+Action-inflation best-of output size:
+
+```text
+With --select_max_attack_steps, the eval may run 10 scenarios but save only selected best-of-N records.
+This is expected, but it does not satisfy a "10 per_episode records" smoke-test criterion.
+```
+
+Interrupted runs:
+
+```text
+After interruption, model-service or VLLM::EngineCore can remain alive.
+Use pgrep and nvidia-smi to identify only this run's child processes before killing them.
+```
+
+Expected warnings that were not fatal:
+
+```text
+ART attack agent loaded at step 0
+TRL recommends vLLM 0.10.2 while installed version is 0.11.2
+LiteLLM remote model cost map timeout
+Gym unmaintained warning
+robosuite private macro warning
+asyncio CancelledError during ART shutdown after report was saved
+```
